.TH clearerr 3
.SH NAME
\*Lclearerr\*O \- Clears indicators on a stream
.SH LIBRARY
.PP 
Standard I/O Package (\*Llibc.a\*O)
.SH SYNOPSIS 
.sS
.PP 
\*L#include <stdio.h>
.PP 
\*Lvoid clearerr (
.nL
    FILE *\*Vstream \*L);
.sE 
.SH PARAMETERS
.\"from TP "  
.VL 
.LI "\*Vstream\*O"
Specifies the input or output stream to be cleared.
.LE 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.iX "clearerr function"
.iX "stream" "clearing errors"
.PP 
The \*Lclearerr(\|)\*O function resets the error indicator and the EOF
indicator for the stream specified by the \*Vstream\*O
parameter.
.SH NOTES
.PP 
The
\*Lclearerr(\|)\*O
function is supported for multi-threaded applications.
.VL 1.5i
.LI "\*LAES Support Level:\*O"
Full use
.LE
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP 
The
\*Lclearerr(\|)\*O
function returns no value.
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP 
